    "Andreas \"Andy\" von Bechtolsheim is cofounder and chief architect of network switching company Arista Networks. He owns a nearly 17% stake in the business that he has earmarked for his heirs.",
    "Much of his fortune stems from an early $100,000 investment in Google.",
    "Following SEC charges of insider trading, Bechtolsheim agreed - without admitting guilt - to a five-year ban on serving as an Arista director or officer.",
    "In 1982, he cofounded tech hardware firm Sun Microsystems with Bill Joy, Scott McNealy and Vinod Khosla. Oracle bought Sun in 2010 for $7.4 billion.",
    "Born in Germany, Bechtolsheim studied computer engineering at Carnegie Mellon University and received his PhD from Stanford University."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Besides Arista, Bechtolsheim cofounded two other IT networking companies with David Cheriton (one sold to Sun Microsystems, another to Cisco).",
    "Bechtolsheim invented one of the first network workstations while studying for his Ph.D."
  ]
